  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 23-year-old woman with asthma is brought to the emergency department because of shortness of breath and wheezing for 20 minutes. She is unable to speak more than a few words at a time. Her pulse is 116/min and respirations are 28/min. Pulse oximetry on room air shows an oxygen saturation of 92%. Examination of the lungs shows decreased breath sounds and scattered end-expiratory wheezing over all lung fields. Treatment with high-dose continuous inhaled albuterol is begun. This patient is at increased risk for which of the following adverse effects?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Hypoglycemia"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Hypokalemia"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Sedation"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Urinary frequency"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Bradycardia"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=GN0Bcg&anker=Z350eb8cd29b2f98aee1fae10a72648e9\" data-learningcard-id=\"GN0Bcg\" data-anker=\"Z350eb8cd29b2f98aee1fae10a72648e9\" data-sememe-id=\"wn0hvg\">β2 agonists</a> have a multifactorial effect on glucose <span data-sememe-id=\"3uXSI-\">homeostasis</span> by stimulating <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=t60X5S&anker=Zf5dc7e344560a17e1e1eb6bb8ddda83e\" data-learningcard-id=\"t60X5S\" data-anker=\"Zf5dc7e344560a17e1e1eb6bb8ddda83e\" data-section-id=\"iucJIV0\" data-sememe-id=\"PhXWVB\">glycogenolysis</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=260T4S&anker=Z0842648c05a9f12b182c77d4baeb7a3a\" data-learningcard-id=\"260T4S\" data-anker=\"Z0842648c05a9f12b182c77d4baeb7a3a\" data-sememe-id=\"AdXRsC\">pancreatic</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Gm0BSg&anker=Z22bb3029af932ca3214f211adb89e9e3\" data-learningcard-id=\"Gm0BSg\" data-anker=\"Z22bb3029af932ca3214f211adb89e9e3\" data-sememe-id=\"LL0wyg\">insulin</a> secretion, and thereby promoting <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pg0Wv2&anker=Z2073da4b63c47c15dfe991223a4d9cd2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pg0Wv2\" data-anker=\"Z2073da4b63c47c15dfe991223a4d9cd2\" data-sememe-id=\"b40H3T\">hypoglycemia</a>. However, because there is a simultaneous release of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=260T4S&anker=Z0842648c05a9f12b182c77d4baeb7a3a\" data-learningcard-id=\"260T4S\" data-anker=\"Z0842648c05a9f12b182c77d4baeb7a3a\" data-sememe-id=\"AdXRsC\">pancreatic</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=260T4S&anker=Zee82769cbb8a350ab35aba8d36b7f104\" data-learningcard-id=\"260T4S\" data-anker=\"Zee82769cbb8a350ab35aba8d36b7f104\" data-section-id=\"TFc6hV0\" data-sememe-id=\"l9bvnD\">glucagon</a> and a decrease in <span data-sememe-id=\"H2dKQ60\">insulin sensitivity</span>, the net effect of β2-mediated stimulation is <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3g0SE2&anker=Z41765cf0097c7ea6f788430b14b10a35\" data-learningcard-id=\"3g0SE2\" data-anker=\"Z41765cf0097c7ea6f788430b14b10a35\" data-section-id=\"8I0Oeh\" data-sememe-id=\"41W3S40\">hyperglycemia</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) CORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lI0v1h&anker=Z1454fccf44cdd1776601d443f63ca03c\" data-learningcard-id=\"lI0v1h\" data-anker=\"Z1454fccf44cdd1776601d443f63ca03c\" data-sememe-id=\"gG0FAh\">Hypokalemia</a></b></span> is a common adverse effect of continuous <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=GN0Bcg&anker=Z4a4150a87542490cc222fcb6f3f2bd8a\" data-learningcard-id=\"GN0Bcg\" data-anker=\"Z4a4150a87542490cc222fcb6f3f2bd8a\" data-section-id=\"7Ib4VE\" data-sememe-id=\"hRac54\">albuterol</a> therapy. It is caused by <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=GN0Bcg&anker=Z350eb8cd29b2f98aee1fae10a72648e9\" data-learningcard-id=\"GN0Bcg\" data-anker=\"Z350eb8cd29b2f98aee1fae10a72648e9\" data-sememe-id=\"wn0hvg\">β2-agonist</a> <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>stimulation of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=9o0NVS&anker=Zf80a4b23fbd47262f17c28c75f79f5d9\" data-learningcard-id=\"9o0NVS\" data-anker=\"Zf80a4b23fbd47262f17c28c75f79f5d9\" data-section-id=\"epcxoW0\" data-sememe-id=\"Pg0Wv2\">Na<sup>+</sup>/K<sup>+</sup>-ATPase</a></b></span>, which leads to an intracellular K<sup>+</sup> shift. Additionally, β2-mediated stimulation of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a> elevates <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qo0C1S&anker=Z64a7426bbad2bf440e8e5d9e67c2a51a\" data-learningcard-id=\"qo0C1S\" data-anker=\"Z64a7426bbad2bf440e8e5d9e67c2a51a\" data-section-id=\"QocubW0\" data-sememe-id=\"VGbGyE\">cAMP</a> levels, thereby increasing <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=t60X5S&anker=Zf5dc7e344560a17e1e1eb6bb8ddda83e\" data-learningcard-id=\"t60X5S\" data-anker=\"Zf5dc7e344560a17e1e1eb6bb8ddda83e\" data-section-id=\"iucJIV0\" data-sememe-id=\"PhXWVB\">glycogenolysis</a> and <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3g0SE2&anker=Z41765cf0097c7ea6f788430b14b10a35\" data-learningcard-id=\"3g0SE2\" data-anker=\"Z41765cf0097c7ea6f788430b14b10a35\" data-section-id=\"8I0Oeh\" data-sememe-id=\"41W3S40\">hyperglycemia</a></b></span>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3g0SE2&anker=Z41765cf0097c7ea6f788430b14b10a35\" data-learningcard-id=\"3g0SE2\" data-anker=\"Z41765cf0097c7ea6f788430b14b10a35\" data-section-id=\"8I0Oeh\" data-sememe-id=\"41W3S40\">Hyperglycemia</a> stimulates <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Gm0BSg&anker=Z22bb3029af932ca3214f211adb89e9e3\" data-learningcard-id=\"Gm0BSg\" data-anker=\"Z22bb3029af932ca3214f211adb89e9e3\" data-sememe-id=\"LL0wyg\">insulin</a> secretion, which also activates the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=9o0NVS&anker=Zf80a4b23fbd47262f17c28c75f79f5d9\" data-learningcard-id=\"9o0NVS\" data-anker=\"Zf80a4b23fbd47262f17c28c75f79f5d9\" data-section-id=\"epcxoW0\" data-sememe-id=\"Pg0Wv2\">Na<sup>+</sup>/K<sup>+</sup>-ATPase</a> and further potentiates the intracellular K<sup>+</sup> shift. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lI0v1h&anker=Z1454fccf44cdd1776601d443f63ca03c\" data-learningcard-id=\"lI0v1h\" data-anker=\"Z1454fccf44cdd1776601d443f63ca03c\" data-sememe-id=\"gG0FAh\">Hypokalemia</a> can cause <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=pl0LBT&anker=Zf57bff8d5455c72457da0440f636f4bc\" data-learningcard-id=\"pl0LBT\" data-anker=\"Zf57bff8d5455c72457da0440f636f4bc\" data-sememe-id=\"jn0_Gg\">EKG</a> changes, such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=pl0LBT&anker=Z59877cde7bf58740a01493e8f3817758\" data-learningcard-id=\"pl0LBT\" data-anker=\"Z59877cde7bf58740a01493e8f3817758\" data-section-id=\"rNcfc10\" data-sememe-id=\"thbXft\">T wave</a> flattening, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=pl0LBT&anker=Zb02c148203e50dada0a8ef560f44e6f7\" data-learningcard-id=\"pl0LBT\" data-anker=\"Zb02c148203e50dada0a8ef560f44e6f7\" data-section-id=\"ZWcZPY0\" data-sememe-id=\"nKY7SJ\">ST depression</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lI0v1h&anker=Zd7268891be09ea1cb1ba6baa7b25d4d9\" data-learningcard-id=\"lI0v1h\" data-anker=\"Zd7268891be09ea1cb1ba6baa7b25d4d9\" data-section-id=\"1j12zg0\" data-sememe-id=\"khXmVB\">U waves</a>.<br><br>Other adverse effects of continuous <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=GN0Bcg&anker=Z4a4150a87542490cc222fcb6f3f2bd8a\" data-learningcard-id=\"GN0Bcg\" data-anker=\"Z4a4150a87542490cc222fcb6f3f2bd8a\" data-section-id=\"7Ib4VE\" data-sememe-id=\"hRac54\">albuterol</a> therapy include <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sq0t-S&anker=Zd4e2194d3ccbce7ba40364b7d381b6cd\" data-learningcard-id=\"sq0t-S\" data-anker=\"Zd4e2194d3ccbce7ba40364b7d381b6cd\" data-sememe-id=\"umbph8\">hypomagnesemia</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Eq08Zh&anker=Ze24842c03e01aa3db6e30faa35e27c76\" data-learningcard-id=\"Eq08Zh\" data-anker=\"Ze24842c03e01aa3db6e30faa35e27c76\" data-sememe-id=\"4hX3VB\">hypophosphatemia</a>, and increases in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zo0reS&anker=Z5187178e03db14012e904aa6c4b15de8\" data-learningcard-id=\"zo0reS\" data-anker=\"Z5187178e03db14012e904aa6c4b15de8\" data-section-id=\"tpcXrW0\" data-sememe-id=\"bLXHwA\">heart rate</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=GN0Bcg&anker=Z350eb8cd29b2f98aee1fae10a72648e9\" data-learningcard-id=\"GN0Bcg\" data-anker=\"Z350eb8cd29b2f98aee1fae10a72648e9\" data-sememe-id=\"wn0hvg\">β2 agonists</a></span> often cause irritability, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kP0mUT&anker=Z6ed492871b68b31189bcb84adbfe1e96\" data-learningcard-id=\"kP0mUT\" data-anker=\"Z6ed492871b68b31189bcb84adbfe1e96\">anxiety</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=x30Ekf&anker=Z31783b886c5b864e996ac90b710d2de9\" data-learningcard-id=\"x30Ekf\" data-anker=\"Z31783b886c5b864e996ac90b710d2de9\" data-sememe-id=\"7O04FT\">tremor</a>, not sedation, through their effects on the <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lp0vpS&anker=Z0111aade770ed6f7d136b455de1d6c1f\" data-learningcard-id=\"lp0vpS\" data-anker=\"Z0111aade770ed6f7d136b455de1d6c1f\" data-section-id=\"1Cc2Ie0\" data-sememe-id=\"6SXj0B\">central nervous system</a></span> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=so0tWS&anker=Z6f7ea6c70fce86b21d8ffeb1772bdfe0\" data-learningcard-id=\"so0tWS\" data-anker=\"Z6f7ea6c70fce86b21d8ffeb1772bdfe0\" data-section-id=\"HzcK8U0\" data-sememe-id=\"FRXgKB\">skeletal muscle</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>β-mediated stimulation of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Rp0l6S&anker=Zb39fa0c160d5f2d2d45d0f06da0f4fcf\" data-learningcard-id=\"Rp0l6S\" data-anker=\"Zb39fa0c160d5f2d2d45d0f06da0f4fcf\" data-section-id=\"qwcCPe0\">bladder</a> causes relaxation of the <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Rp0l6S&anker=Za60885f9e7b627bd7950f40f4acc824b\" data-learningcard-id=\"Rp0l6S\" data-anker=\"Za60885f9e7b627bd7950f40f4acc824b\" data-section-id=\"qwcCPe0\" data-sememe-id=\"kSXm-x\">detrusor muscle</a></span>. This effect delays the need for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Rp0l6S&anker=Z1cb08fa60b75cadec38829ba7e1c22b7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Rp0l6S\" data-anker=\"Z1cb08fa60b75cadec38829ba7e1c22b7\" data-section-id=\"qwcCPe0\" data-sememe-id=\"6NWjXN0\">micturition</a> and results in decreased <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kg0mv2&anker=Z4696f8e500da3c30710da62453f005f8\" data-learningcard-id=\"kg0mv2\" data-anker=\"Z4696f8e500da3c30710da62453f005f8\" data-section-id=\"iJXJF_\" data-sememe-id=\"hfbcNG\">urinary frequency</a></span>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=GN0Bcg&anker=Z350eb8cd29b2f98aee1fae10a72648e9\" data-learningcard-id=\"GN0Bcg\" data-anker=\"Z350eb8cd29b2f98aee1fae10a72648e9\" data-sememe-id=\"wn0hvg\">β2 agonists</a></span> cause <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rM0fJg&anker=Z3ae4e1e5581c7405590e65b57fa82021\" data-learningcard-id=\"rM0fJg\" data-anker=\"Z3ae4e1e5581c7405590e65b57fa82021\" data-section-id=\"KVcUvY0\" data-sememe-id=\"lNbvY8\">tachycardia</a></span>, not <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rM0fJg&anker=Zd260d8e17660a21cb9baf0a449c178d7\" data-learningcard-id=\"rM0fJg\" data-anker=\"Zd260d8e17660a21cb9baf0a449c178d7\" data-section-id=\"KVcUvY0\" data-sememe-id=\"Fh0gff\">bradycardia</a></span>, through a combination of direct β1-mediated cardiac stimulation and <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cm0aeg&anker=Z3b8592aa617b0299e2269ed032a13773\" data-learningcard-id=\"cm0aeg\" data-anker=\"Z3b8592aa617b0299e2269ed032a13773\" data-section-id=\"hGbc_E\" data-sememe-id=\"FAbglw\">reflex tachycardia</a></span> following β2-mediated peripheral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jJ0_FS&anker=Zda019e8b85958113f73c96b53cdae51f\" data-learningcard-id=\"jJ0_FS\" data-anker=\"Zda019e8b85958113f73c96b53cdae51f\" data-section-id=\"NZ1-b20\" data-sememe-id=\"3DXSVZ0\">vasodilation</a>. Accordingly, <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=GN0Bcg&anker=Z350eb8cd29b2f98aee1fae10a72648e9\" data-learningcard-id=\"GN0Bcg\" data-anker=\"Z350eb8cd29b2f98aee1fae10a72648e9\" data-sememe-id=\"wn0hvg\">β2 agonists</a></span> should be used with caution in patients with known cardiovascular disease (e.g., <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Xh09cf&anker=Zce0d4554dd0bc7f9fba742d2827ffc63\" data-learningcard-id=\"Xh09cf\" data-anker=\"Zce0d4554dd0bc7f9fba742d2827ffc63\" data-sememe-id=\"Pk0WLT\">hypertension</a></span>, <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rS0faf&anker=Z07d22fa4c3f9da63ddf39683e4eaa845\" data-learningcard-id=\"rS0faf\" data-anker=\"Z07d22fa4c3f9da63ddf39683e4eaa845\" data-sememe-id=\"ak0QmT\">heart failure</a></span>) because they can induce life-threatening <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7S04af&anker=Zccf8a75c2bd0cf1f6323e31e0496b4d6\" data-learningcard-id=\"7S04af\" data-anker=\"Zccf8a75c2bd0cf1f6323e31e0496b4d6\" data-section-id=\"lmcvf10\" data-sememe-id=\"CE0qB3\">ventricular arrhythmias</a></span>.</div>",
      "hint": "Albuterol is a β2-agonist. At typical doses (e.g., from a metered-dose inhaler), albuterol does not typically have systemic effects. However, use of continuous inhaled albuterol for long periods of time can result in β2-mediated adverse effects.",
